===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|profit|lang=enm}} < {{etyl|fro}} {{term|profit|lang=fro}} (French: {{term|lang=fr|profit}}). < {{etyl|la}} {{term|profectus||advance, progress, growth, increase, profit}} < {{term|proficere||to go forward, advance, make progress, be profitable or useful}}; see [[proficient]].

===Pronunciation===
* prŏf'it, /ˈprɒfət/, /"prQf@t/
* {{audio|en-us-profit.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: '''Homophones''': [[prophet]]
* {{rhymes|ɒfɪt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Total [[income]] or [[cash flow]] minus [[expenditure]]s. The [[money]] or other [[benefit]] a non-governmental organization or individual receives in exchange for products and services sold at an advertised price.

====Usage notes====
When the difference is negative the term [[loss]] is correct.  ''Negative profit'' does appear in [[microeconomics]].
Profit by a government agency is called a surplus.

